cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG 

This paper deals with developing an algorithm for automatic detection of dialogue acts in Twitter customer service conversations. This involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval techniques, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper proposes heuristics for negation handling, which is a sub-topic of sentiment analysis (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
